    <entry xml:lang="en">
        <title>Image Shortcodes</title>
        <published>2021-05-19T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2021-05-19T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        <author>
          <name>Unknown</name>
        </author>
        <link rel="alternate" href="https://abridge.netlify.app/overview-images/" type="text/html"/>
        <id>https://abridge.netlify.app/overview-images/</id>
        
        <summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;This post covers the &lt;strong&gt;imghover and img shortcodes&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;. Images can also be embedded directly using markdown &lt;code&gt;![Ferris](ferris.svg)&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;, but it is better to use a shortcode so you can explicitly set the width and height, this will help prevent content layout shift which improves user experience and the google lighthouse score.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
</summary>
        
    </entry>
